
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsec-lla-only-11.txt'>
    <title>"Using Only Link-Local Addressing Inside an IPv6 Network", Michael Behringer, Eric Vyncke</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-opsec-lla-only-11.txt</link>
    <description>In an IPv6 network it is possible to use only link-local addresses on infrastructure links between routers.  This document discusses the advantages and disadvantages of this approach to help the decision process for a given network.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-09-25T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
